All patients and families have the right to have complete information regarding diagnosis, prognosis and treatment in a language you understand. They strive to provide their services in the languages of their patients and families. Their Spanish language interpreting services are especially strong; they employ 16 full-time Spanish interpreters to meet your and your child’s needs. In-person and video remote sign-language interpreters may be scheduled in advance, but can also be reached for emergency needs by contacting the manager of Interpreting Services, Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m. to 5 p.m., or the administrative coordinator during all other hours. They also have a video remote interpreting system, provided by In-Demand Interpreting. The system allows them to connect at any time with interpreters that know the following languages: American Sign Language, Arabic, Cantonese, Mandarin, Polish, Somali, Spanish, Vietnamese.
